      "sacrifices": "Slight latency increase per write (one additional DB call). If the application writes to MongoDB outside the repository (raw queries), those writes won't be captured. Dual-write is not truly atomic across both stores.",
      "alternatives_considered": [
        "CDC with Debezium: Captures all changes at the database level, including raw queries. But requires Kafka + Debezium infrastructure — massive operational overhead for a 200 writes/min workload.",
